ize:12pt"> when coming from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Newquay is on the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">left while two villages Cubert and Crantock which is on the right side of this main road enjoy a better bus service then we do.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There buses run every half hour and they also enjoy an evening service up to mid-night and also a Sunday serv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ice while our village has only an hourly service finishing at 1645 from Newquay and from Truro 1810.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> We do not have even a Sunday bus service and our village is the same size if not bigger then the two above mentioned villages.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There is also a similar bu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s service which runs from Mitcheal a village only 2 miles from ours.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They in fact have two different bus companies serving them and they too enjoy an evening and Sunday service.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> And they are much smaller then oursleves.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There is even a bus service in Z</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ela a little hamlet with less then a quarter of the popluation then Newlyn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">East.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They in fact have a bus service every half hour.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I think it disgusting that we as concil tax payers should have to pay concil tax to subsidise these villages that enjoy a m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uch better service then we do.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They say our route is not viabley commercial, well neither is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the other villages.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The only time Cubert and Crantock are busy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is in the summer months of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">June, July and August.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The rest of the year they get the same amount o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f people getting on them as we do yet there service never alters.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Many times the early buses do not turn up-they are supposed to start the service going to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Truro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">from our village at 0710.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Yet on several occasions the 0710, 0810 and the 0910 never turned </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">up and there</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">were people waiting to get to work, college, doctors and dentist appointment and even jury duty.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Many young people have left our village because</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">when they get</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a job they have to leave it or else they are sacked because they</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">can't get to work </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on time.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What the use of having a bus service which cannot be relied on.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> A timetable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is a legal contract between the passenger and the bus company.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They can't just say they don't have a bus to put on because then they become in breach of contract.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fares to get to Truro are £4.50 for an adult and around £2.90 for a child.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> If a young mothert had to go shopping in the city she would have to pay £7.40 just to pick up the essentials and she is not even sure that a bus will turn up to take her!!</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pensioner and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I have to wait on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1010 bus, but many times this bus doesn't turn up or if it does turn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">up it's full.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They give priorty to the people in Newquay.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The bus company wouldn't even think to save maybe five spaces for us.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I once asked an offical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">who works for Western Greyhound the bus company that servies our village, why don't they do this so atleast some of us would have a change to get on the bus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and there answer was that the people at Newquay would then have to wait another 45 minutes for a b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">us well what about us, we would have to wait for an hour!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> But he didn't seem to care.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Why should he, he lives in Newquay.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I was waiting for the 1010 to show up</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and when it did it was full.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There were 9 people plus myself waiting to get on the bus.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was a freezing morning in March</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> most of the people waiting were between 70-85 years of age and one man had to make a hospital appointemt to be examined for an empending heart operation.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> This man was inferm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and had trouble standing up for too long even</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with a can you can see he was shaking from the strain of standing up and waiting for this bus.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> You could tell he was in pain but he was old and sick and too tired to fight the bus company so he turned and walked away stooped, dejected. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Probably going h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ome to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">call the hospital and tell them he can't</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">make his appointment again because he had to cancel the week</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">before for the same reason.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This is not an islocated insident it happens on a regular basis.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span s